<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,424,595]" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Vazquez, Tribouillier &amp; Archila" authorityYear="2021" box="[136,327,424,450]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="javieri">
<emphasis box="[136,327,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Magnolia javieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[505,528,425,450]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">M</emphasis>
. sect. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[603,712,424,450]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[603,712,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Magnolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[914,1061,424,450]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="archilana">
<emphasis box="[914,1061,424,450]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">M. archilana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also from 
<collectingRegion box="[1192,1341,424,451]" country="Guatemala" name="Alta Verapaz" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Alta Verapaz</collectingRegion>
, differing from the latter in its smaller, abaxially glabrous leaves vs. abaxially ferruginous-pubescent on the veins, apex deeply emarginate vs. round, apiculate; smaller flowers and fruits (
<tableCitation box="[796,878,496,522]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="3.[136,202,640,666]" captionTargetBox="[144,1431,678,1082]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of Magnolia javieri with M. archilana and M. guatemalensis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF26661D1065946AFF6CFD62FBE2FD43" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" tableUuid="DF26661D1065946AFF6CFD62FBE2FD43">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Another similar species is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Donnell-Smith" authorityYear="1909" box="[1194,1391,496,522]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Magnoliaceae" genus="Magnolia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="3" pageNumber="60" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guatemalensis">
<emphasis box="[1194,1391,496,522]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">M. guatemalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingRegion box="[176,465,532,559]" country="Guatemala" name="Alta Verapaz" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Alta Verapaz Department</collectingRegion>
. It differs in its longer petiole, smaller leaves and abaxially glabrous, shorter peduncles, smaller flowers, sepals and petals, fewer stamens, glabrescent polyfollicles and more carpels.
</paragraph>
